title: 中国语录

//我反对在中文室使用太多的单词。To my blind eyes, one of the most noble possible notions of the Chinese Language boils down to a radical attempt at unification through symbols. Regardless of language game [[infinigress]]ive problematics, I admire the notion of collectively holding literal symbols well and the expensiveness of shaping [[The Other]] with integrity. I can only understand the tiniest fraction, and it will be the wrong perspective no matter what I do. What can I say? Thank you for showing me, this is very interesting, and I am doing what I can to understand given what little I have here. I only hold and look through a tiny shard of [[The Great Human Conversation]].//

